  "texts": [
    "(4)Figure 10 shows the selectivity distributions of the generated range queries across different datasets.",
    "We categorize the set of generated query boxes R based on selectivities into three groups: (a) low selectivity (sel(R) ≤ 1%), (b) middle selectivity (1% < sel(R) ≤ 5%), and (c) high selectivity (sel(R) > 5%).",
    "For query boxes in each selectivity group, we report the average query time in subsequent evaluations.Extension to Box Geometries.",
    "As discussed in Sect. 2.1, all learned indexes in this benchmark are designed for point geometries.",
    "However, since indexing bounding boxes is essential in many real-world spatial applications, we extend each point-based index to support querying box geometries."
  ],
